1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 a6 5. c4 Nf6 6. Nc3 Bb4 (6... Qc7 {
NOTICE! is our move order} 7. Be2 Bb4 8. O-O O-O 9. Qd3) 7. Qd3 O-O 8. Be2 Qc7
9. O-O {By a different move order we have reached our line.} Nc6 10. Nxc6 {
White does not have many more alternatives} (10. Nb3 {was played by Bacrot.
Black should continue with the natural:} Ne5 11. Qg3 (11. Qd4 Nc6 $11) 11... d6
{which puts white under a big dilemma. He is facing the loss of the e4 pawn by
Bxc3 and also the c4 pawn. It seems white has to continue with} 12. c5 $1 Bxc3
13. cxd6 Qxd6 14. Rd1 (14. Qxc3 Nxe4 15. Qe3 Nf6 16. Qg3 Ne4 $11) 14... Qc7 15.
Qxc3 Qxc3 16. bxc3 Nxe4 17. Bb2 Ng6 18. Bd3 Nf6 19. c4 $44 {white has
compensation but no more} e5 20. Nc5 Re8) (10. Bg5 Be7 {the threat is Ng4!} 11.
Bh4 (11. Rac1 Ng4 $15) 11... Ne5 12. Qg3 d6 13. Rac1 b6 14. Nb3 Bb7 15. Nd2 h6
$1 {with a good position for black. Das, A (2399)-Karthikeyan, M (2530)
Hastings ENG 2016}) 10... dxc6 11. Bg5 Be7 12. Be3 (12. Qg3 {does not offer
white any advantage} Qxg3 13. hxg3 e5 14. Be3 b5 $11 {1/2-1/2 (14) Guerra
Mendez,J (2542) -Magem Badals,J (2534) Barcelona ESP 2017}) 12... b5 $1 13.
Rac1 (13. a3 e5 {followed by Be6}) 13... b4 14. Nb1 c5 $15 15. Nd2 e5 {This
move can wait, for as much as black wants} (15... Bb7 16. Qc2 a5 {black is
better}) 16. Qc2 Bb7 17. Rfd1 a5 18. f3 Nd7 19. Nf1 Nb8 20. Bd2 Nc6 {We can
conclude that the opening has been a great success for black and the move 9.
Qd3 does not offer white much of an advantage.} 21. Ne3 Nd4 22. Qd3 Bg5 23. Nd5
Qd8 24. Bf1 Ra6 25. Bxg5 Qxg5 26. Qe3 Qh5 27. Rd2 Rh6 28. h3 Kh8 29. Rf2 Qh4
30. f4 exf4 31. Qxf4 Qxf4 32. Rxf4 Re6 33. Bd3 f6 34. Ra1 Bc6 35. a3 Nb3 36.
Rd1 Rb8 37. Rf2 Ree8 38. g4 Nd4 39. axb4 axb4 40. Ra1 h6 41. Ra5 Nb3 42. Ra6
Nd4 43. Ra5 Nb3 44. Ra6 Bd7 45. Rd6 Rb7 46. Nf4 Kg8 47. Ng6 Re6 48. Rd5 Be8 49.
e5 Bf7 50. Rd8+ Re8 51. Rxe8+ Bxe8 52. Be4 Ra7 53. Bd5+ Bf7 54. exf6 gxf6 55.
Rxf6 Bxd5 56. cxd5 Kg7 57. Rb6 Nd2 58. Ne5 Re7 59. Rg6+ Kf8 60. Rf6+ Kg7 61.
Rf5 Rxe5 {0-1 (61) Anand,V (2779)-Ivanchuk,V (2747) Doha QAT 2016 [Castellanos,
R]} *

