{CONCLUSION: The move 9.Bc3 presents problems for the black of difficult
solution. Black could refrain from the capture on d4 on the earlier move, but
then other problems arise. I have provided all ideas I had, and to be honest,
with an engine in hand white seems to be better in all lines. Nevertheless,
let's not underestimate the practical chances in these positions, after all,
black is taking risks since the moment he plays 4...a6! 0-1 (32) De la Paz
Perdomo, F (2433)-Milov, V (2665) Morelia 2007 CBM 116 ext [Castellanos,R]} *

