1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 a6 5. Be2 b5 {Keeping in the style of
the previous variation I advocate this move with the thematic idea of Ne7-Nbc6
later on. Let's see some of the white's main continuations, I must warn you
that it is very important to learn the right move orders in this variation.} (
5... Nc6 {leads to the Taimanov variation}) (5... Nf6 6. Nc3 d6 {leads to
Schveningen territory}) 6. a4 b4 7. O-O (7. e5 Qc7 8. Bf3 Bb7 9. O-O Nc6 {
is a safe route to equality} ({I chose} 9... Ne7 $5 10. Nd2 Ng6 (10... Nbc6 $1
11. Nc4 Ng6 $11) 11. Bxb7 Qxb7 12. Nc4 Nc6 13. Nf3 Be7 14. Bg5 $5 (14. Be3 O-O
15. Qd3 {is more solid and here black should play} f6 16. Rad1 Rac8 $1 17. Qxd7
(17. exf6 gxf6 $13) 17... Qxd7 18. Rxd7 Nb8 19. Rd4 Nc6 20. Rd3 Ncxe5 21. Nfxe5
Nxe5 22. Nxe5 fxe5 23. Rc1 Bc5 $1 {with equal chances in the rook endgame})
14... O-O 15. Bxe7 Ncxe7 16. b3 Nd5 17. Qd4 Qc7 (17... f6 $1 $132) 18. Nfd2 f6
$132 {Forcen,D (2501)-Castellanos,R (2508) Ciudad de Zaragoza 12+3 2013}) 10.
Nxc6 Bxc6 11. Nd2 Ne7 (11... Qxe5 12. Bxc6 dxc6 13. Nc4 Qe4 14. Nd6+ Bxd6 15.
Qxd6 Ne7 16. Be3 Nf5 17. Qc5 Qd5 18. Qxb4 Nxe3 19. fxe3 c5 20. Qf4 O-O {
with equality}) 12. Nc4 Ng6 13. b3 $6 (13. Bxc6 Qxc6 14. b3 Be7 15. Bb2 O-O $11
) 13... Nxe5 14. Nxe5 Qxe5 15. Bxc6 dxc6 16. Be3 Bc5 17. Qf3 O-O 18. Rad1 Rad8
19. g3 Bxe3 20. Qxe3 {Antoli Royo,J (2441)-Cacho Reigadas,S (2520) Monzon ESP
2016} Qxe3 21. fxe3 c5 $17 {black would have been clearly better}) 7... Bb7 8.
Nd2 (8. Bf3 Nc6 (8... Ne7 $5 9. c3 (9. Nd2 Qc7 {when it transposes to my game
against Forcen mentioned above.}) 9... Nbc6) 9. Nxc6 Bxc6 10. Nd2 Nf6 11. Re1
Rc8 (11... Qc7 $5) (11... Be7) (11... d5 {are all interesting ways to continue}
) 12. Nb3 Qc7 13. Bd2 Be7 (13... d5 14. e5 Ne4 $132) 14. c3 {Zubarev,A (2511)
-Milov,V (2676) Baku 2007} bxc3 15. Bxc3 O-O {looks good for black}) 8... Qc7
9. Re1 Nf6 10. e5 Qxe5 $1 11. Bxa6 Qd5 12. Bxb7 Qxb7 13. a5 (13. Nb5 d5 14. Nb3
Be7 15. Bf4 O-O 16. Nc7 Ra7 $11) 13... Be7 14. Nc4 O-O 15. Nb6 Ra6 16. Be3 d5
17. Qe2 h6 18. Qb5 Nfd7 19. Nb3 Rc8 20. Qd3 Rc6 $11 21. Bd4 Rc7 22. c4 bxc3 23.
bxc3 Nc6 24. Nxd7 Rxd7 25. Bb6 Ra8 26. Qb5 Rd6 27. Rab1 Qc8 28. h3 Na7 29. Qd3
Rc6 30. Rec1 Bf6 31. Bd4 Bg5 32. Qg3 {1/2-1/2 (32) Ovcharenko,L (2271)-Catt,P 
(2402) ICCF 2012 OM Corr 201701 [Castellanos,R]} *

